Croatian international defender Ivan Strinic has left AC Milan by mutual consent after just one season during which he never played after being diagnosed with a heart condition, the Italian club announced on Monday. <img class="aligncenter  wp-image-1245791" src="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Strinic.jpg?resize=640%2C397&#038;ssl=1" alt="Strinic" width="640" height="397" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Strinic.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Strinic.jpg?resize=300%2C186&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Strinic.jpg?resize=768%2C477&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Strinic.jpg?resize=1024%2C636&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Strinic.jpg?resize=58%2C36&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Strinic.jpg?resize=260%2C161&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Strinic.jpg?resize=200%2C124&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Strinic.jpg?resize=160%2C100&amp;ssl=1 160w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Strinic.jpg?resize=560%2C348&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/08/Strinic.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" />The 32-year-old left-back — a key member of the Croatian team that reached the World Cup final in 2018 — joined Milan from Sampdoria just after the tournament on a two-year deal. But he failed to make any appearances for the seven-time European champions after being diagnosed with early signs of hypertrophy, a thickening of the heart muscle, shortly after his arrival. READ ALSO: Bale returns as Zidane stays tight-lipped on Neymar “AC Milan announces the termination by mutual consent of the contract with the defender Ivan Strinic,” the Serie A team said in a statement. “The club wishes the footballer every success in his future career.” The defender has been linked with a possible move to Serie A rivals SPAL or Parma. Strinic, who has 49 caps, played six of Croatia’s seven World Cup games in Russia as they reached final where they lost 4-2 to France. He started his career with Hadjuk Split in his native Croatia and also played in France and Ukraine before joining Serie A side Napoli in 2015, and Sampdoria in 2017 and AC Milan in 2018. VANGUARD Seven-time reigning champions Juventus beat Lazio 2-0 and last season's runners-up Napoli came from two goals down to edge AC Milan 3-2 as the Italian league favourites both continued their perfect start to the season with a maximum six points after two games. August 27, 2018 In "Sports" Croatia coach Zlatko Dalic on Monday named a 24-man World Cup squad, which will be eventually reduced by one player, and is led by international stars Luka Modric, Ivan Rakitic and Mario Mandzukic. May 21, 2018 In "Sports" AC Milan's new sporting director Leonardo revealed Thursday that team captain Leonardo Bonucci wants to return to Juventus just one season after signing for the club from the Serie A champions. July 26, 2018 In "Sports"